## Fluxos Principais

### 1. 🔐 Autenticação

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  actor U as Usuário
  participant FE as Frontend
  participant MW as Middleware
  participant AUTH as NextAuth v5
  participant DB as PostgreSQL

  U->>FE: Acessar /login
  alt Google OAuth
    FE->>AUTH: signIn("google")
    AUTH->>AUTH: Redirect Google
    AUTH->>DB: PrismaAdapter cria/busca User+Account
    AUTH->>FE: JWT Token (session)
  else Credentials (email/senha)
    FE->>AUTH: signIn("credentials", {email, password})
    AUTH->>DB: findUnique(email)
    AUTH->>AUTH: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    AUTH->>FE: JWT Token (role incluído)
  end
  FE->>MW: Acessar rota protegida
  MW->>MW: Verifica JWT (session.user.role)
  alt Não autenticado
    MW->>FE: Redirect /login
  else É rota admin e role ≠ admin
    MW->>FE: Redirect /dashboard
  end
```

**Pontos-chave:**
- Sessão via **JWT** (obrigatório com Credentials + PrismaAdapter)
- O `role` do usuário é injetado no token via callbacks [jwt](file:///c:/Users/luis.albuquerque/Desktop/simulados/simulaeduca/src/lib/utils/auth.ts#71-95) → [session](file:///c:/Users/luis.albuquerque/Desktop/simulados/simulaeduca/src/lib/utils/auth.ts#95-103)
- Middleware protege rotas: `/dashboard/*`, `/simulados/*`, `/creditos/*`, `/configuracoes/*`, `/admin/*`

---

### 2. 📝 Geração de Simulado (Fluxo Principal)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  actor P as Professor
  participant FE as SimuladoForm
  participant API1 as POST /api/simulados
  participant API2 as POST /api/simulados/gerar
  participant CRED as Credits Module
  participant GEN as Question Generator
  participant RAG as RAG Retriever
  participant LLM as OpenAI GPT-4o
  participant VAL as Question Validator
  participant LLM2 as GPT-4o-mini
  participant DB as PostgreSQL

  P->>FE: Preenche formulário + seleciona descritores
  FE->>API1: POST {title, teacher, evaluation, subject, grade}
  API1->>DB: Exam.create(status: "draft")
  API1-->>FE: {examId}

  FE->>API2: POST {examId, descriptors[{id, difficulty}]}
  API2->>CRED: hasEnoughCredits(userId, N)
  CRED->>DB: User.creditsBalance ≥ N?

  loop Para cada descritor (1-30 questões)
    loop Até 4 tentativas
      API2->>GEN: generateQuestion(input)
      GEN->>RAG: retrieveRelevantChunks(query)
      RAG->>DB: SELECT ... WHERE embedding <=> vector ORDER BY similarity LIMIT 5
      RAG-->>GEN: chunks contextuais
      GEN->>GEN: buildQuestionGenerationPrompt()
      GEN->>LLM: Enviar prompt (até 3 retries internos)
      LLM-->>GEN: JSON {stem, options, answer, justification}

      GEN-->>API2: GeneratedQuestion
      API2->>VAL: validateQuestion(question, descriptor)
      VAL->>VAL: validateStructure() — checks locais
      VAL->>LLM2: buildValidationPrompt() — validação semântica
      LLM2-->>VAL: {isValid, errors}

      alt isValid = true
        Note over API2: Aceitar questão ✓
      else Falhou mas tem fallback
        Note over API2: Usar bestFallback
      end
    end

    API2->>DB: ExamQuestion.create()
    API2->>DB: QuestionBank insert (reutilização futura)
  end

  API2->>CRED: deductCredits(userId, N, examId)
  CRED->>DB: Transaction: User.decrement + CreditTransaction.create
  API2->>DB: Exam.update(status: "completed")
  API2-->>FE: {success, questionsGenerated}
  FE->>FE: router.push(/simulados/{examId})
```

**Pontos-chave:**
- **1 crédito = 1 questão gerada**
- Cada questão passa por **até 4 tentativas** de geração (com **3 retries internos** no generator para JSON malformado)
- Se o validator LLM rejeitar todas, usa o `bestFallback` (primeira questão estruturalmente válida)
- Questões são salvas no `question_bank` para reutilização futura

---

### 3. 📄 Geração de PDF

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  actor P as Professor
  participant FE as Detalhe do Simulado
  participant API as GET /api/simulados/pdf
  participant PDF as PDF Generator
  participant DB as PostgreSQL

  P->>FE: Clica "Baixar Prova" ou "Baixar Gabarito"
  FE->>API: GET ?examId=...&type=exam|answer_key
  API->>DB: Exam + Questions + Descriptors
  API->>PDF: generateExamPdf(data) ou generateAnswerKeyPdf(data)
  PDF->>PDF: React-PDF renderToBuffer (layout A4)
  PDF-->>API: Buffer PDF
  API-->>FE: Response (application/pdf, attachment)
```

Gera dois documentos distintos:
- **Prova**: cabeçalho (escola, turma, data) + questões com alternativas
- **Gabarito**: grid de respostas + resoluções por questão

---

### 4. 📚 Pipeline RAG (Ingestão de Materiais)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  actor A as Admin
  participant FE as Knowledge Base
  participant API as POST /api/admin/ingest
  participant EXT as Extractors
  participant SPL as Text Splitter
  participant EMB as OpenAI Embeddings
  participant DB as PostgreSQL

  A->>FE: Upload arquivo (PDF/DOCX/TXT) + metadados
  FE->>API: FormData {file, descriptorCode, subject, grade}
  API->>EXT: extractFromPdf/Docx/Txt(buffer)
  EXT-->>API: texto extraído
  API->>SPL: RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(1000 chars, 100 overlap)
  SPL-->>API: chunks[]
  API->>EMB: generateEmbeddings(chunks) — batch
  EMB-->>API: vectors[] (1536 dims cada)

  loop Para cada chunk
    API->>DB: INSERT material_chunks (content, embedding::vector, metadata)
  end

  API-->>FE: {chunksCreated: N}
```

